   "built" -> "{2026, 2, 22, 11, 14, 16.132072}", 
    "history" -> {"14.3", "", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {"fermionic quantum computation"}, "specialkeywords" -> {}, 
    "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> "QuantumMob/Q3",
     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "WickOdds[v -> 0][in] returns out -> p, where out is the Wick state \
resulting from the fermionic Gaussian supermap \\[Rho] \\[RightTeeArrow] d \
\\[Rho] d^\\[Dagger] with probability p := \
\\[LeftDoubleBracketingBar]v\\[RightDoubleBracketingBar] 2, and d := \
\\[CapitalSigma]i vi ai is a (unnormalized) dressed mode and ai are bare \
fermion modes. WickOdds[v -> 1][in] returns out -> p for process \\[Rho] \
\\[RightTeeArrow] d^\\[Dagger] \\[Rho] d with p := \
\\[LeftDoubleBracketingBar]v\\[RightDoubleBracketingBar] 2. WickOdds[v -> \
2][in] returns out -> p for process \\[Rho] \\[RightTeeArrow] (d^\\[Dagger] \
d) \\[Rho] (d^\\[Dagger] d) with p := \
\\[LeftDoubleBracketingBar]v\\[RightDoubleBracketingBar] 4. WickOdds[v -> \
3][in] returns out -> p for process \\[Rho] \\[RightTeeArrow] (d \
d^\\[Dagger]) \\[Rho] (d d^\\[Dagger]) with p := \\[LeftDoubleBracketingBar]v\
\\[RightDoubleBracketingBar] 4. WickOdds[{..., vi -> si, ...}][in] returns \
{..., outi -> pi, ...} for the fermionic Gaussian supermap \\[Rho] \
\\[RightTeeArrow] \\[CapitalSigma]i Fi \\[Rho] F_i^\\[Dagger], where the \
Kraus operator Fi is specified by vi -> si.", "synonyms" -> {}, 
    "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "WickOdds", "titlemodifier" -> "", 
    "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> "WickOdds", "type" -> "Symbol", 
    "uri" -> "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/WickOdds"}},
